page.title: 19THICK BARE WOOD
page.content: Just east of the road running out to the Buckingham, Bletchley Road, there is a small woodland called Thick Bare Wood. This area is said to be just as most of the land was like in older days. 12 of us went along a muddy track to get to the wood. When we got to the wood we found it very difficult to get into the centre as the trees were dense and the undergrowth was thick. The trees were mostly deciduous. We spotted sycamore, oak, elder, hawthorn, hazel trees and masses of honeysuckle. We saw a hare running in the wood and it is well known that in the middle of the wood the small deer known locally as "Barking Deer" have their home.
